    "message": "\nahhh yes...  the age old question:  What do I want to be when I grow up?\n\nand now that you've \"grown up,\" you feel like you should have arrived somewhere.\n\ncogitate on this:\n\nlife has no meaning.  you are born, you eat, you poop, you do some\n\nstuff, and then you die.  the only meaning to your life is how it\n\nmatters to those around you.  your only lasting impact is the love you\n\nleave.\n\nthe journey is the destination\n\nsay it with me.\n\nThe journey *is* the destination.\n\nwrite music not because it matters to anyone else, but because it\n\nmatters to you.\n\nStudy what fascinates you, no matter if the world approves or needs\n\nyour research, but because it enriches *you*\n\nstop looking outside for peace, find it in yourself.\n\nI write bad music.\n\n\nI make little movies.\n\nin the big picture, those things don't matter to anyone else.  but I like them.\n\nand that matters.\n\nthe journey is the destination.\n\ngo live.\n\nPeople on their death bed never say, \"Gee, I wish I'd spent more time at work.\"\n\nblue skies, black death\n",
