    "message": "\nRelax. Take a deep breath. You're going through one of the many \"stages\" of life. There will be a similar existential crisis at approximately each subsequent decade of your life.\n\nYou're absolutely correct-- nothing is permanent. Nobody will likely remember you or your contribution during your short time on Earth after a generation or so. I hardly knew my grandparents and I never knew about anyone prior to their generation. Who might they have been? What did they accomplish? I'll never know.\n\nEveryone currently alive right now is a cohort for this time. This brief instant in eternity. Some will check out early, some will live long and see much. Some will accomplish great things that may be remembered for long periods of time. Most won't.\n\nSo why do it? Why live? This brief moment of consciousness is a gift. A Unique gift. Sentience and self-determination. So, music and biology fell through. Big deal. find other things that interest you and pursue them. Travel. See the world and it's varying cultures. Experience love and loss. Embrace the comfort of friends and family. Start your own family and gain some immortality in surest possible way. In the end, these are the most important things in life. The rest is irrelevant. Is that really so terrifying or depressing? Think of the immensity of space and time-- you're forever a part of it.\n\nWhatever you do, don't fall into the trap that religion has both the answers and life eternal. You will squander your precious time being alive if you buy-in to the promise of life eternal after death.\n\nFocus.",
