    "subject": "Listserve response",
    "tags": [
      "Altruism",
      "Nihilism"
    ],
    "message": "\nEvery moment of your life is a miracle. Stop planning for your legacy; it's like you're already dead.\n\nDo what you enjoy. Do you like music? Yes. Then play music. Do you like biology? No. Don't be a biologist.  Seems like you got it half right; you should not have given up the music.\n\nDo what moves you, and do your best. Do it repeatedly, and your best will improve, and perhaps someone will appreciate it in your lifetime. Meanwhile, do it for yourself, for the process, for your own experience of it.\n\nHaving a life goal to \" expand the boundaries of human knowledge and to create a permanent record of my thoughts passed down through the ages.\" is --at best-- a vague and narcissistic childish daydream.   \n\nEnough of this grandiose codependence. Live your life so that it's good enough for YOU. Billions of extraordinary lives never make it into the public record, and millions of stupid and mediocre lives do.  Life your life to have experiences. That's all life is: the chance to have experiences.\n\nYou want to help humanity? Volunteer at a soup kitchen, or any non-profit.\n\nIf you want to be free from suffering, study Buddhism, or for a more contemporary look at similar concepts, read:  \"The Power of Now\"\n\nGood luck stopping trying to find meaning in your life!",
