    "message": "\nHi {{ name }}, just read your post, and I have to say I was getting goosebumps the whole time as I am going through a very similar experience. A little background, I am a 33 y/o pediatrician, and also majored in bio, thinking I would change the world if I became a doctor, which hasn't exactly been the case (never thought I would spend most of my time trying to convince crazy parents that their kids belly pain was just really bad constipation, not the necrotizing bacteria they read about on the news...) i also have/had a passion for music, thinking i would incorporate that into my quest to save humanity, but aside from playing in a cover band with a few fellow docs i haven't made much of that either. I just finished training last year (finally!) and fro a financial perspective am pretty comfortable (if not extraordinarily wealthy) but i find myself at a huge crossroads similar to what you described, wondering if the life i have now is worth the years i sacrificed to get to this point. i often do feel like i have been a spectator to my own life for quite some time now, and have reached the point where i feel like i need to take a more active role in the world around me, i just have to figure out how to do that... anyway, thanks for sharing your story, i would love to keep this conversatrion going if at all possible.!\n\n \n\nBest,",
