    "message": "\nStop thinking about the impact that you need to have on humanity as a whole. Precious few people in the world will have an impact beyond their time on this planet. Even fewer 100 years later, and still fewer 1000 years after that. If your goal is to be one of those few, then you are almost assuredly destined to failure. You might try playing the lottery.\n\nThink about all the people you know well who have had some close personal influence in your life, either positively or negatively. Realize that probably none of them will be remembered in 100 years, yet they were still able to make a difference in some way to YOU. This is important. You wouldn't be who you are today without them. You wouldn't be reading this email without them.\n\nFind what you love above all else, because that's what you're going to spend most of your time doing. Also, you're not going to be able to be truly great at anything you don't love. Start doing that thing, and do it the best you possibly can. Be proud of your work. Your effect on those around you will inspire some of them to do THEIR thing the best they can, and so on. I believe the best thing we can hope for in humanity is for each person to be able to do what they love, and to do it to the best of their ability.\n\nYou may not move mountains or be remembered for eternity, but as long as you do what you love and do it well, you'll be happy while you're on this Earth and you'll make better contributions as you go.\n\nGood luck.",
