    "message": "\nHi {{ name }},\n\nI appreciated reading your post today, partly because I'm about to turn 30 and do occasionally feel similar concerns, except that I haven't exactly \"established\" myself yet (I returned to school for architecture last fall) and therefore haven't proven my limits per say, but do get a glimpse of them often, seeing more talented people around.\n\nAnd we can't all be geniuses, despite being brought up to think that we can be. And it's easy to think that, if only we found that one special area, we could really make a difference in the world.\n\nWhy I write though, is to say that small actions make a big difference. Going through life being kind to the people around you and promoting good karma, can perhaps have a more profound effect on the world than writing that influential piece of music or other \"significant contribution\".\n\nFind fulfillment in the small things and others will be inspired by that energy.",
