    "message": "\nHi {{ name }},\n\nI'm 65 and still learning about life. But I understand your problem. Perhaps you are expecting too much of longevity for your ideas. If you consider that you can influence, rather than merely leave some monument to your achievements, you may find greater satisfaction. \n\nI'll fill that out a bit. Few of us will attain the longevity of Shakespeare in what we leave behind. Even world-famous prophets like Buddha, Mohammed and Jesus have suffered from the distortion of their original thoughts and words. Probably the best we can do is influence those who come after us; influence them toward the ideas and philosophies we feel are important, good and productive. I'm a believer in justice, so I incorporate that theme into my writing. Some will get it (many will fail to see the message, of course) but those who do see it will absorb the idea and, probably subconsciously, incorporate it into their lives, words and deeds. It's the most we can hope for. \n\nThe simple, cliched but no less true ambition can really only be to leave this world a better place than you found it.\n\nEnjoy your life; it's the only one you'll have.\n\nRegards,",
