    "message": "\nDear {{ name }},\n\nI absolutely know where you are coming from.\n\nI have felt similarly at times in my life. \n\nOf all the advice I could offer from my own experience, this is perhaps the essence of it:\n\nMeaning is found in the heart. Thoughts are like an endless circle, and in my experience will never lead to a deep sense of purpose. That deep sense comes from the heart.\n\nPerhaps begin to pay attention to your heart, and how it feels. How does it feel right now? Bring your attention there. What sensations, what emotions do you notice?\n\nThen begin to pay attention to how your heart feels at different times, and in response to various things. When something makes your heart sing, seek there. If your heart is singing always, you will be at peace in this world, and you will be in joy.\n\nHere is something else to try. You can do it right now. \n\nClose your eyes, and draw your attention inside. \n\nLocate that place or feeling inside you that feels that \"curious meaninglessness.\" There is wisdom here. \n\nGo deeper into that feeling. \n\nWhat do you find? \n\nWhat do you see in your mind's eye, what do you feel? Identify it. \n\nThen go deeper. \n\nGo deeper.\n\nFurther beneath, what do you feel, what do you find? Identify it. Feel it. Experience it.\n\nGo to the universal source within you. Let it express itself. Feel its nature.\n\nGo through all the layers until you find the source.\n\nIf you did this exercise, or have thoughts or questions or responses in general, I would be happy to hear from you.\n\nBless you,",
    "cleaned": true,
    "title": "Go Deeper",
    "quote": "Go to the universal source within you. Let it express itself. Feel its nature.\n",
